Good afternoon, our first School Site Council meeting is today at 3:30 p.m. We will be discussing the purpose of the SSC, electing officers and member selections, and reviewing bylaws. Participating in School Site Council will allow teachers, school staff, administration, parents, and community members to monitor our school goals and help make BOCS the best school! If you are interested please join us today through the Google Meet link that was sent and shared through ParentSquare, thank you.

Buenas tardes, nuestra primera reunión del Consejo del Plantel Escolar es hoy a las 3:30 p.m. Discutiremos el propósito del SSC, la elección de funcionarios y miembros, y la revisión de los estatutos. ¡Participar en el Consejo del Plantel Escolar permitirá a los maestros, personal escolar, administración, padres y miembros de la comunidad monitorear nuestras metas escolares y ayudar a que BOCS sea la mejor escuela! Si está interesado, únase a nosotros hoy a través del enlace de Google Meet que se envió y compartió a través de ParentSquare, gracias.

Este es solo un recordatorio amistoso para los estudiantes de que iniciará sesión en Google Classroom todos los días para que pueda completar las tareas y unirse a la reunión en vivo de las 9 am en Google Meet. post_text: Juneteenth is the oldest nationally celebrated commemoration of the ending of slavery in the United States. Dating back to 1865, it was on June 19th that the Union soldiers, led by Major General Gordon Granger, landed at Galveston, Texas with news that the war had ended and that the enslaved were now free. Note that this was two and a half years after President Lincoln’s Emancipation Proclamation - which had become official January 1, 1863. The Emancipation Proclamation had little impact on the Texans due to the minimal number of Union troops to enforce the new Executive Order. However, with the surrender of General Lee in April of 1865, and the arrival of General Granger’s regiment, the forces were finally strong enough to influence and overcome the resistance.
text: Juneteenth is the oldest nationally celebrated commemoration of the ending of slavery in the United States. Dating back to 1865, it was on June 19th that the Union soldiers, led by Major General Gordon Granger, landed at Galveston, Texas with news that the war had ended and that the enslaved were now free. Note that this was two and a half years after President Lincoln’s Emancipation Proclamation - which had become official January 1, 1863. The Emancipation Proclamation had little impact on the Texans due to the minimal number of Union troops to enforce the new Executive Order. However, with the surrender of General Lee in April of 1865, and the arrival of General Granger’s regiment, the forces were finally strong enough to influence and overcome the resistance.

Que tengas un gran día.

Happy Friday BOCS students. Today spirit day theme is "Beach Day". Simple as it sounds let's do it! Put on your beachwear, get your towels, sandwiches, and sunblock, and let's have beach day! Also, I hope you all know this is the last day of school, so enjoy our summer, and be safe - and this isn't our final good-bye post so keep a lookout!!

Feliz viernes estudiantes de BOCS. Hoy el tema del día del espíritu es "Día de playa". ¡Tan simple como suena, hagámoslo! Ponte tu ropa de playa, toma tus toallas, sándwiches y protector solar, ¡y tengamos un día de playa! Además, espero que todos sepan que este es el último día de clases, así que disfruten de nuestro verano y estén seguros, y este no es nuestro último mensaje de despedida, ¡así que estén atentos!

Caption: There comes a time when silence is betrayal and Ingenium will not betray the communities that we serve by being silent during this time. \
We stand with our communities in stating that we want an end to Police Brutality and we believe that Black lives matter.

Llega un momento en que el silencio es traición e Ingenium no traicionará a las comunidades a las que servimos al permanecer en silencio durante este tiempo.
Apoyamos a nuestras comunidades al afirmar que queremos poner fin a la brutalidad policial y creemos que las vidas negras importan.

post_text:
#Wellnesswednesday
Water is always the best choice.
Water should be the beverage that children (over age two) consume most frequently. Serve water with meals and snacks. For variety, try adding pieces of fresh fruit, vegetables, or fresh herbs to create a delicious alternative to plain water.
El agua es siempre la mejor opción.
El agua debe ser la bebida que los niños (mayores de dos años) consumen con mayor frecuencia. Sirva agua con las comidas y meriendas. Para variar, intente agregar trozos de fruta fresca, verduras o hierbas frescas para crear una alternativa deliciosa al agua corriente.

#Wellnesswednesday

Starting tomorrow every, Wednesday, Thursday, and Monday will be BOCS personalized #hashtag post. Mondays will be #Mybrainfoodmonday, Wednesdays will be #Wellnesswednesday, and last Thursday will be #Throwbackthursday. We are looking forward to providing you these beneficial gems and spicing up your news feed. Have a good rest of your day BOCS family.

post_text:
Good afternoon families,

For today's daily video update please click this link.

In the update, I discuss when Chromebooks will be distributed. Please see the schedule below:

Day Time Grades
Monday, April 6th 9-11 a.m. TK, K, 1st, 6th
Tuesday, April 7th 9-11 a.m. 2nd, 3rd, 7th
Wednesday, April 8th 9-11 a.m. 4th, 5th

If you have multiple students, in different grades, you can still come just at one of the assigned days and receive devices for both students. If you were unable to pick up your student's learning packet, you can pick them up on your assigned date as well.

In order to pick up a device for your student, please bring your student with you. If that is not possible, a family member that is listed on the student's emergency card must be present to pick up the device and they must have a valid ID with a picture on it. Devices will be provided utilizing a drive through method. All families will be asked to stay in their cars during distribution.

Be well and be safe.

Best,

Mrs. Smith
